This Caturday kitten is Cat Stevens. Born in September, 2017, Cat Stevens and his Mom and two brothers were rescued from a dump between an apartment complex and a strip center in SW Houston. The people living in this area abuse small animals and the hawks circle looking for food. Cat Stevens and his family were named after favorite musicians by the Vet staff who cared for them. He is a beautiful kitten with a silvery undercoat and slightly longer fur than the rest of his family. Cat Stevens is friendly and playful and fully vetted. Contact HOPE at www.homelesspets.net to meet him.

Adopted!! Scar & Bugsy Together!
These two furrbabies packed their bags and went home for the holidays!! Mom and son came in to finalize Scar's adoption when suddenly Bugsy jumped into their lap - if you've been in the adoption center you know Bugsy isn't shy about asking for love 🤣 Bugsy was meowing as if to say choose me too, and she did! She did not want to split these two furrbabies up after all they have been through together 🐈💙🐈 Bugsy and Scar were strays in Florida that found foster with a vet tech that used to foster for us when she lived in NJ. When the hurricane was coming a few months ago her family came back to NJ with all their pets, including 3 foster kittens. Fern, Bugsy, Scar stayed behind with The Cats Meow Rescue to find furrever homes. Fern was adopted in November and now the boys have found their home together! Hip hip hooray!
Congrats Scar, Bugsy and their new family 💙💜 #CatsMeowScar #CatsMeowBugsy #petsmartdelran #adoptlove #petsmartcharities #homefortheholidays #twokittensisbetterthanone #rescuecat #kittens

Meet Shawnee!
Shawnee has a sweet, soft face and a gentle personality to match! She enjoys going for walks with her person, walking elegantly by your side as you explore the neighborhood. As a German Shepherd dog, it's no surprise this girl is also a smarty who loves to work for.. treats! She knows Sit, 'Find it', and comes when called. Shawnee also likes to play fetch-- though her version is taken at a leisurely pace and she seems to enjoy relaxing and chewing the ball more
(**Scroll to see video!) 😉
.
Shawnee came into the shelter on Oct 21, 2017 as an Owner Surrender. No reason for surrender was given, but they did report that she is housebroken, is friendly with small dogs (though fought with her GSD sibling), and is okay in the car and on leash. Shawnee is 5 years old and 85 pounds.
This lovable, friendly girl is ready to join a family on a lifetime of adventures- come meet her today!
💖 Shawnee #A1736835 🐾
*Blue/ Medically Alerted for possible solar dermatitis (on nose).*
----------------------
All North Central animals come spayed/neutered, microchipped and current on all their shots (including rabies). North Central LA City shelter; 3201 Lacy St., Los Angeles, CA; 213-485-5767.
